<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        Hydraulic Brake System
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Hydraulic Brake System</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For troubleshooting brake switch circuit input signals to the engine ECM, refer to the Engine
                    Diagnostic Manual.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0823905" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Hydraulic Brake System</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.39in"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove hydraulic brake relay (300) and measure voltage from circuit 90A to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(300), 90A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in fusible link 90-FL or circuit 90A or 90, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect circuit 90N from reserve pump motor. Install a jumper wire at relay socket
                                (300) from circuit 90A to 90N. At reserve pump motor circuit 90N, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>At motor 90N to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90N, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Touch circuit 90N to reserve pump motor terminal. Does motor run?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper, reconnect 90N. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace reserve pump motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F33 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F33</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F33 circuit 90B, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F33, 90B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90B or dash conn. (2), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F33. Disconnect brake switch conn. (50/51). At (50) measure voltage
                                from circuit 90C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(50), 90C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At stop light switch conn. (51), measure voltage from circuit 70 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(51), 70 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70 or open fuse F9, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance across switch (50) while brake pedal is depressed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across sw. (50).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace brake/stop light switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance across switch (51) with brake pedal depressed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across switch (51).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace brake/stop light switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (50/51) and disconnect diode assembly (48) from conn. (47). At (47)
                                and with brake pedal depressed, measure voltage from circuit 90D to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(47), 90D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect brake monitor module conn. (49), and with brake pedal depressed, measure
                                voltage from 90E to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F3 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F3</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch to ignition position and at F3, measure voltage from circuit 13 to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F3, 13 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 13, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At disconnected conn. (47), measure voltage from circuit 90U to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(47), 90U to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90U, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With multimeter in diode test mode, test diode assembly (48). Do diodes test good?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(48)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>.2 to .6 volt.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace diode assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect diode assembly (47)/(48) and disconnect brake relay (300). Turn key on and
                                at socket (300), circuit 90H, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(300), 90H to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90H or dash conn. (2), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect flow switch conn. and measure resistance across switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across flow switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace flow switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect flow switch conn. and disconnect differential pressure switch conn. (301).
                                At (301) circuit 90L, measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(301), 90L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 90L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (300) circuit 90J, measure resistance to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(300), 90J to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 90J/90K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test hydraulic brake relay (300) by measuring resistance from pin 30 to 87A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(300), pin 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace hydraulic brake relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test hydraulic brake relay (300) by applying +12V to pin 85 and gnd. to pin 86,
                                and measuring resistance from pin 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Energized relay (300), pin 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace hydraulic brake relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At brake monitor module conn. (49), measure resistance from circuit 90M to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90M to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 90M or dash conn. (2), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install brake relay (300). Turn key switch on and depress brake pedal. At conn.
                                (49) circuit 90F, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>24.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With brake pedal depressed and at conn. (49), measure voltage from circuit 90F to
                                90-G.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90F to 90-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 90-G/ 11-G/ 11-GL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>25.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (49) and circuit 90R, measure voltage to ground while an assistant depresses
                                brake pedal.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90R to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90R/70C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With brake pedal depressed and at conn. (49), measure voltage from circuit 90P to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(49), 90P to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90P, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (49) and move key switch to ignition position. Do alarm and brake
                                warning light operate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Hydraulic brake system circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check bulb, buzzer, and parallel circuits 90S and 90T, then replace component or
                                repair circuit(s).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>28.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>If condition persists, refer to CTS-5280, Hydro-Max II Brake Monitor System
                                Troubleshooting Manual
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
